          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p/>
              <p>Single folio on parchment in horizontal format; Qurʾanic text: Q 6:68-75;  Sixteen lines per page; AL-16 and another fragment from the same collection <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/27/verse/19/manuscripts/1944">AL-11</ref> and two other fragments from the Freer Gallery collection <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/35/verse/18/manuscripts/1273">F1945.19</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/26/verse/225/manuscripts/1274">F1945.20</ref> originally belonged to the same codex. For a detailed description of sister fragments of these fragments see  the entry by Marcus Fraser: "Doha, Qatar National Library: <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/46/vers/16?handschrift=1418">HC.MS.2017.0010</ref>".</p>
              <p> Cf. also the website of the institution: https://www.loc.gov/item/2019714726/</p>
              <p/>
            </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="mysql_id_692635" n="1r">
