              <layoutDesc>
                <layout writtenLines="16">16 - 16 lines to a page
                                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc>
              <handNote/>
            </handDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <summary>
                <p>Script: kūfī type B.II. The letter <hi rend="italic">ʾalif </hi>is always vertical, with short return at the baseline in the independent form. The characteristic shape of the letter <hi rend="italic">qāf </hi>in the final position is given with its ending going far to the right. The <hi rend="italic">mašq</hi>-method, the horizontal elongation of the letters, is used in the manuscript. Vocalisation is made by red dots. Diacritical marks are used sparsely, originally only the letter <hi rend="italic">nūn </hi>in the independent position is being marked with a dash. </p>
              </summary>
              <scriptNote>
                                                                kūfī B.II
                            </scriptNote>
            </scriptDesc>
